0 -11 Td
() Tj
0 -11 Td
(Purpose:) Tj
0 -11 Td
(- Define expectations for training and certifications with focus on medical appointment leave and approvals.) Tj
0 -11 Td
(- System of record: TimeTrack. Owner role: Employee.) Tj
0 -11 Td
() Tj
0 -11 Td
(Definitions:) Tj
0 -11 Td
(- Leave Type: Medical Appointment Leave) Tj
0 -11 Td
(- Owner: Employee) Tj
0 -11 Td
(- Evidence: policy exception form) Tj
0 -11 Td
() Tj
0 -11 Td
(Rules:) Tj
0 -11 Td
(1. Submit requests at least 5 working days in advance when feasible.) Tj
0 -11 Td
(2. Carry-forward cap is 5 days unless legal requirement is higher.) Tj
0 -11 Td
(3. More than 4 consecutive days requires manager + HR approval.) Tj
0 -11 Td
(4. Emergency leave must be regularized within 8 days.) Tj
0 -11 Td
(5. Approval decisions must be recorded in TimeTrack with an audit note.) Tj
0 -11 Td
() Tj
0 -11 Td
(Workflow:) Tj
0 -11 Td
(Step A: Employee raises request with dates and reason category.) Tj
0 -11 Td
(Step B: Manager validates staffing impact and approves or rejects with rationale.) Tj
0 -11 Td
(Step C: HR validates entitlement balance and compliance exceptions.) Tj
0 -11 Td
(Step D: System posts balance changes and notifies payroll if applicable.) Tj
0 -11 Td
() Tj
0 -11 Td
(Example Case:) Tj
0 -11 Td
(- Scenario: an employee requests sick leave and submits supporting document after returning) Tj
0 -11 Td
(- Decision cue: prioritize business continuity, fairness, and documented evidence.) Tj
0 -11 Td
